experience.description:
- Facilitate the ROB process with public sector department on a monthly basis
- Own business process and planning for public sector (full year revenue forecasting process; 
- Top deals tracking (more than 1M biz, top public customers);
- Budgeting process ownership ; 
- Full analytical support for director and team)
- Operations management(work on business analysis and opportunities identification; work with Finance & Business Operations on tracking of performance metrics; develop and prepare the business and data insights)
- Own managing and developing of content and communication for presentations to internal and external audiences
- Manage Exec's visits timetable
- Lead special projects, typically those with long-term cross-business impact
- Field readiness process coordination

- Working with upper mid-market «red» customers (ION, Bosco, Tez Tour, Ralf Ringer, Natali Tours, etc.); 
- Ownership of relationship and opportunity management within the assigned accounts; 
- Owns the face-to-face interaction with the customer
- Collect successful track record with customer and Microsoft and transform it into success stories; 
- Ownership of the account planning processes: 
- Create customer opportunity plan, roles and expectations; 
- Execute the plan, regularly check status, debrief and document fulfillment and design wins; 
- Close key opportunities for Microsoft products, technologies and services within the assigned accounts; succeed in winning opportunities against major competitors;
- Ensure post-sales support through Partner Services programs; 
- Constantly update the data in customer database on existing accounts and protocol sales activities to ensure good teamwork; 
- Establish a sales relationship with selected partners engaging them in territory and account planning process;

- Organize agenda items for meetings, attend meetings, take minutes and follow up on action items, manage daily diary of appointments/meetings; prioritize and manage conflicts with respect to diary management and meeting schedules;
- Organize all travel arrangements; screen /field telephone calls received and take accurate messages, arrange extensive telephone and video conferences; 
- Manage expense reports; processing basic accounting (PO); preparation of statistical reports;
- Owns fully executive visits;
- Owns dashboard refresh process;
- Deal with confidential information; 
- Correspondence: drafting letters, emails, memos, faxes etc, following up where required;
- Own team’s kick-off & off sites organization

- Prepare written translations (correspondence, business documents, and office memos); 
- Provide oral translations during internal work meetings, board of directors meetings, and all other instances; 
- Provide oral translations during external business meetings with clients; 
- Participate in and coordinate various department projects 
- Participation in international exhibitions 
- Solving administrative problems
- Special projects ownership (“plastic surgery”, publishing house Olma-Press)
- later – assistance for finance & credit controller
